Will this scroll as the list gets longer?
</user_query>"}]},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes, absolutely! The `LazyColumn` composable is designed to handle scrolling automatically as the list grows. Here's why your implementation will scroll properly:

1. **`LazyColumn`** is a vertically scrolling list that:
 - Only composes and lays out visible items (lazy loading)
 - Automatically enables scrolling when content exceeds the available height
 - Efficiently handles large lists by recycling views

2. **Your current setup** in the `MenuList` composable:
 ```kotlin
 LazyColumn(
 modifier = modifier.padding(16.dp),
 verticalArrangement = Arrangement.spacedBy(12.dp)
 ) {
 items(menuItems) { item ->
 // Card items...
 }
 }
 ```
 The `Modifier.fillMaxSize()` passed from `MainContent` ensures the `LazyColumn` takes up all available space, and as you add more menu items, it will automatically become scrollable when the content height exceeds the screen height.

So yes, as you add more topics to your `menuItems` list (2, 5, 10, 100+ items), the menu will scroll smoothly without any additional configuration needed. The same applies to the selected screen content if it uses a scrollable composable like `LazyColumn` or a regular `Column` with `Modifier.verticalScroll()`."}]},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"
